[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This step consumes raw ADT registration records (one per arrival) and buckets them into hourly counts per ED per ESI level. In production this is an AWS Glue Streaming job that reads from Kinesis, applies a watermark for late-arriving records, and writes hourly Parquet partitions to S3. The demo does the equivalent in plain Python over the in-memory list so you can trace what each transform accomplishes.
