[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m class PoissonGLM:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Pedagogical stand-in for a Poisson regression on hourly counts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Real production uses statsmodels' GLM with the Poisson family
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     or a negative binomial model when the data is overdispersed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The demo uses a coordinate-descent on the squared-error
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     objective with a log link to keep the math readable. The
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     interface (fit, predict, sigma) is what matters: any model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     that produces a point forecast plus a residual standard
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     deviation drops in.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
